@chebee7i No problem for me. The only thing I find a little bit confusing is now that `None` and `'none'` mean two different things. 
And then I come back to what I already said :-), I do not really see the need for the `None` option for default (the other ipython directive parameters also do not have that option + it would simplify the code). For me, it would be more logical that `None` would mean no import of matplotlib. But as I said, it doesn't really matter to me, I wouldn't use it.

Does Sphinx itself use the 'None is default' paradigm?
